<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-11-15T23:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-11-15T23:36:00-05:00" n="950" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d950">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/19883</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Vera Cruz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-11-15T22:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 15, 1916, 10 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Now learned no American casualties Inter-Oceanic accident except those
                            mentioned my November 14, 6 p.m. Vera Cruz State military commander
                            sends messenger to tell me he will punish severely soldiers for
                            wholesale robbing wounded and killed in wreck.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Canada</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>